17/11/2008
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- The cabinet remains opposed to UN Secretary-General Ban Ki-moon's plan for deploying the EU mission, EULEX, in Kosovo, according to statement issued on Sunday (November 16th).
"The government ...
reconfirms its resolute commitment to implement [Martti] Ahtisaari's comprehensive proposal in its entirety and throughout the territory of Kosovo.
In this regard, the government is committed to further co-operation with international organisations in Kosovo that work for the good of Kosovar citizens," said the statement.
Prime Minister Hashim Thaci also reiterated his opposition to the plan, saying "Our position is the protection and respect of the constitution." (Zeri, Koha Ditore, Lajm, Kosova Sot - 17/11/08)
